dataIdInfo.idAbs:
/* shoreline

--all layers projected to UTM 37 S

--ESI line geometry made by...

--all coastline within 7km converted to grid cell of 200m

--convert all input layers to grid with 200m cell usinf coastline mask

--combine coastal landcover type, shoreline and mangrove datasets

--scan east-west and west-east

--identify sequences of shoreline type and individual types and assign

sensitivity values, according to table XX, to output grid

--for each 200m cell along the ESI line assignto that cell the hihest

sensitivity value of any cell withon a 2km radius

--reclassify according to low, medium, high

/* bio features

humpbackwhales turtle Seahorses_points Dugong Coelacanth_c dolphin_sites

whaleshark Iba_ims_tz INTpol_RWB NATpnt_IUCN NATpnt_NoIUCN

NATpnt_notdesignated NATpol_IUCN NATpol_NoIUCN NATpol_notdesignated

/* human/economic features

saltpans_points seaweed Sport_fishing_sites MR_Fish_prawn_culture_points

MR__tz_zan_fls_MR_points MG_hotels_points tz_dive_sites3

Tz_Historical_sites INTpnt_RWB shipping1 shipping2 Tz_settlement

-- using ranks contained in table YY

-- repeated first for biological featres and then for human/social

features...

--convert to grid (cell size 500m) replaicing observation location with

sensitivity value

--sum all input grids

--smooth combined grid by assigning individual cell the maximum value of

surrounding cells within 5km radius

--normalise cell values by dividing by maximum

--intersect with ESI line geometry (used for shoreline)

--reclassify to low,medium, high according to table ZZ

--now produce combined line...

--normalise shoreline line.

--sum lines

--normlise combined line

--reclass low, medium, high accoding to table ...

--create combined grids by adding normlaised bio, human and shoreline grids

-------------
